speakers:



### Katharine Jarmul

Katharine Jarmul is an international speaker focused on topics such as ethics in data science and machine learning. She has spoken at large technical conferences since 2010.

### Matteo Guzzo

_This is what Matteo says:_

Pythonista and freelancer. Originally a Physicist. Having fun with ML Engineering and MLOps.
I hate doing the same thing twice. I love a good crème caramel.

### Sieer Angar

Sieer is an experienced founder, serial entrepreneur and Managing Director with a demonstrated history of working in the information technology and services industry. He is a specialised and strong business development professional with a Master of Science (M.Sc.) focused in Geography, Geo-Eingineering, Geo-IT and Political Science from Ruprecht-Karls-Universität Heidelberg.

### Marielle Dado



### Emily Gorcenski
---
abstract:


Working in the 21st century is very different from the past. Especially the digital space offers many opportunities to work in the office and remotely. In your hometown or somewhere else on the globe.  Some companies even work completely remotely.  Or, as a freelancer, you can be your own boss. Or running a company, where you are in charge of all the decisions. This panel invites folks with diverse careers to ponder the differences in these choices and give advice to you (and their former selves!) on choices along the way.
---
full_description:


In this panel we would like to highlight the different aspects.

* Academia vs Industry
* What are the career paths?
* Employee vs Freelancer vs Founder
* What does it mean to be a consultant (independent or employed)?
* What if I want to start my own company?
* Has Corona changed any of these options significantly?


- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
